						<summary>

						<p>North wall of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> (right of entrance) in front of the central shrine in the Vīraṭṭāṉēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rāstrakūta, Krishna III Year 20 = 959 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This records the gift of 15 kaḻañju of gold, by Vīranaraṇiyār, the mistress <hi rend="italic">(Bhōgiyār)</hi> of Sri Vikramādityaṉ, for a perpetual lamp to the deity Tiruvīraṭṭānattāḷvār of Tirukkōvalūr, in Kuṟukkaikūṟṟam, a district of Malāḍu. The gold was left in the hands of the <hi rend="italic">Nagarattār</hi> of Tirukkōvalūr, who agreed to maintain the gift, with one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of oil daily.</p>						

						</summary>
